    {
      "actionDate": "2026-04-20",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in Senate",
      "text": "<p><strong>America Grows Act of 2026</strong></p><p>This bill permanently funds several agencies that perform agriculture research.</p><p>The bill provides specified funding for the following agencies within the Department of Agriculture:</p><ul><li>the Agricultural Research Service,</li><li>the Economic Research Service,</li><li>the National Agricultural Statistics Service, and</li><li>the National Institute of Food and Agriculture.</li></ul><p>The bill exempts the funding from sequestration, which is a process of automatic, usually across-the-board spending reductions under which budgetary resources are permanently cancelled to enforce specific budget policy goals.</p><p>It also exempts the budgetary effects of the funding from the Statutory Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2010 (PAYGO) and the Senate PAYGO rule.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-05-12T10:27:16Z",
      "versionCode": "00"
    }
  ]
